<center><big>'''Stillwater Haven is one of the anomalous levels of the Backrooms.'''</big></center>

<div style="background-color: rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); border: 5px solid rgba(0,0,0,0); font-size: 35px; margin: 1em; padding: 5px 30px; text-align: center;">Environment</div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0); border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); font-size: 15px; margin: 1em; padding: 10px 30px;">
<br>
<center><div style="display: inline-block; border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4);">[[File:静水.jpeg|450px|center|link=]]</div></center>
<center>'''≫ It's beautiful here, isn't it? ≪'''</center>
<br>
<center>Stillwater Haven manifests as an ocean, a soft, tranquil expanse of water stretching on without bound. The level automatically generates distinct instances for each entrant, containing no threats of any form, only the serene night and the entrant themselves exist, with nothing beneath the surface. Thus, it is recognized as one of the few universally safe havens within the Backrooms.</center><br>
<center>The entire level lies beneath a vast sea of stars, adorned with occasional wispy clouds. It is reported that there is no day-night cycle, and the time has lost its meaning and ceased to flow, freezing everything in the most beautiful moment before dawn. Furthermore, the entrant's metabolic functions are suspended, and one may choose to stay for a minute, an hour, a day, a week, or even a year, without experiencing hunger, cold, or fatigue, nor being troubled by any concerns.</center><br>
<center>The ocean spans a nearly infinite area, its horizon always hidden within the starry curtain, never reached by anyone, leaving the level's true boundaries unexplored. Typically, the entrant's view is obstructed by mountains lying at the seam of sea and sky, however, approaching them never shortens the distance, indicating that these mountains are merely illusions projected by the level to conceal the true scenery behind them.</center><br>
<center>Investigations reveal that the seawater's properties are identical to fresh water in [[The Frontrooms]], constant temperature, cool but not biting, and exceptionally clear. Uniquely, for unknown reasons, the buoyancy provided by this water is significantly greater than that of fresh water. The water level remains below the knees, with the deepest points not reaching the waist, whether walking, squatting, lying down, or prone, one will never be submerged. The current is extremely slow and silent, creating only faint ripples when the entrant attempts to move.</center><br>
</div>

<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin: 1em;">{{Blurquote|quote-text=Open your eyes.<br>It is the water, the soft water, that laps over your ankles, gently holds your body afloat.<br>There is no hustle, no quarrels, no accusations, nor those overwhelming expectations and disappointments that once suffocated you.<br>Standing in the water, your first reaction is not relief, but panic.<br>You try to move forward, hoping the water will deepen enough to submerge you completely, and put an end to everything.<br>But the water always stays below your knees.<br>When you struggle hard, it gently supports you;<br>When you try to lie down, it steadily catches you;<br>When you want to cry, your tears drip into the water, only spreading a faint ripple before being quietly carried away by the current, leaving no trace at all.|image=Asphyxia2.jpeg}}</div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0); border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); font-size: 15px; margin: 1em; padding: 10px 30px;">
<br>
<center><div style="display: inline-block; border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4);">[[File:112efa2ed17f292fb722c3d7ad51a7b3.jpeg|450px|center|link=]]</div></center>
<center>'''≫ You still hold so many unfulfilled wishes, why give up now? ≪'''</center>
<br>
<center>The water surface remains as calm as a mirror all year round, clearly reflecting the figure of the entrant.‌ The bottom of the water body is covered with soft fine sand, with a small number of rock blocks of varying sizes scattered among it, and turquoise aquatic plants occasionally growing in the crevices of the stones.‌ Tiny white or pink petals often float on the water surface, carrying a very faint delicate fragrance and drifting slowly with the current, their origin remains unknown to date, and no phenomena such as decay or sinking have ever been observed on them.‌</center><br>
<center>A faint orange-yellow glow lingers permanently on one side of the level's horizon, and it is presumed that the level is designed to mimic the dawn in [[The Frontrooms]]. However, no celestial body has ever been observed rising from that glowing area up to now. Identical to the distant mountains, the glowing area will always maintain a constant distance from the entrant, and it is neither completely out of reach nor easily accessible, even though this distance will gradually shorten as the entrant moves.</center><br>
<center>The seawater appears to carry a mild soothing effect, which can slowly calm the entrant's intense emotions and prompt them to briefly forget all their worries. Meanwhile, the environment within the level is generally believed to be formed by the things in the entrant's mind being materialized and then merging with the original ocean. This means the entrant may witness scenes related to their own precious memories gradually emerging beneath the water, on the water surface, or even in the sky, which will further soothe their inner mind.</center><br>
</div>

<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin: 1em;">{{Blurquote|quote-text=Most likely, you fell in the moment your foot missed its step.<br>You begin to walk forward slowly.<br>Not to escape, nor to persist, but simply because you no longer wish to remain stationary.<br>The water continues to gently hold you afloat.<br>A white petal drifts quietly to your hand, and you reach out and lift it softly to your nose.<br>So soft, so fragrant.<br>In a daze, you recall those things you ignored in reality, those tiny, insignificant things:<br>The sunlight falling on your quilt at dawn, gentle and warm;<br>A cup of hot tea held in your palms during winter, comforting and shielding against the cold;<br>A kitten by the roadside gently rubbing against your shoes, cute and affectionate.<br>The warmth invisible to you amidst your daily pain now emerges one by one on the water's surface.<br>For the first time, you ask yourself:<br>Will you truly give up like this?<br>Give up the meals yet to be eaten, the sunrises yet to be witnessed, the days yet to be kind to yourself?<br>Give up that self who, despite the pain, was also incredibly brave?<br>The water offers no answer, only gently nudging you a little closer toward the light.|image=Asphyxia3.jpeg}}</div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0); border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); font-size: 15px; margin: 1em; padding: 10px 30px;">
<br>
<center><div style="display: inline-block; border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4);">[[File:岸.jpeg|450px|center|link=]]</div></center>
<center>'''≫ Look, how far you've traveled already? ≪'''</center>
<br>
<center>At the same time, as the entrant's will to continue living deep in their heart gradually becomes clear and firm, the water level will automatically grow shallower step by step along with their footsteps, the water recedes inch by inch from their legs, and the faint orange-yellow glow on the horizon will also draw closer gradually, eventually, a stone-built shore will emerge from the dim night, dry and solid.</center><br>
<center>Unlike the sandy beaches full of coarse gravel in [[The Frontrooms]], the shore of this level is a long embankment paved with grayish-white bluestones. The surfaces of these stones are flat and smooth. A small amount of unidentified moss, presenting an almost transparent emerald green, often grows in the gaps between the stones. The roaring sound of waves slamming against stones has vanished completely here, leaving only the soft, faint sound generated when the water recedes, like a silent farewell to the entrant. On the shore, you can often spot the outlines of many man-made buildings, yet none of these structures are within reach.</center><br>
<center>If they keep moving forward, the entrant will be able to leave Stillwater Haven. Normally, the entrant will not be teleported immediately upon exiting the level, instead, they can stand on the shore for as long as they like, quietly looking back at the boundless still water behind them, only when they are truly mentally prepared to return to the human world will they go back to their original dimension. After returning to the original dimension, the entrant will reappear at the exact location and time roughly five minutes before they entered the level.</center><br>
</div>

<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin: 1em;">{{Blurquote|quote-text=The water level drops from your knees to your calves, and then to your ankles.<br>The glow draws nearer and grows warmer. Gradually, the outline of the shore begins to come into focus.<br>One second. One minute. One quarter. One hour.<br>You finally reach the shore. The instant your toes touch the stone embankment, the heavy burden in your heart that has weighed you down for so long suddenly lifts.<br>Look back.<br>The entire ocean gazes at you silently from behind, with layers of gentle ripples spreading out.<br>You are not superfluous.<br>You are not abandoned.<br>You are the one caught by the water, illuminated by the light, and worthy of living on.<br>You were just too tired, too painful, and in too great a need of a proper embrace.<br>And this body of water has caught you, holding all the warmth that the world never had the chance to express to you.|image=Asphyxia4.jpeg}}</div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); border: 5px solid rgba(0,0,0,0); font-size: 35px; margin: 1em; padding: 5px 30px; text-align: center;">Entity Presences & Human Activities</div>
<div style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0); border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); font-size: 15px; margin: 1em; padding: 10px 30px;">
===<center>Entity Presences</center>===
<center>No entities of any form in the Backrooms exist within Stillwater Haven.‌</center><br>
===<center>Human Activities</center>===
<center>‌Due to the unique properties of Stillwater Haven, only the entrant themselves exists within the level, and the establishment of any colonies or outposts remains merely a fantasy.‌</center><br>
</div>

<div style="background-color: rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); border: 5px solid rgba(0,0,0,0); font-size: 35px; margin: 1em; padding: 5px 30px; text-align: center;">Entrances & Exits</div>
<div style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0); border: 5px solid rgba(var(--theme-border-color--rgb),0.4); font-size: 15px; margin: 1em; padding: 10px 30px;">
===<center>Entrances</center>===
<center>Attempting to take your own life in any dimension, including [[The Frontrooms]], carries a high probability of bringing you to Stillwater Haven, otherwise, you will enter [[After Life]].</center><br>
<center>It is alleged that a special location leading here exists within [[Oceanic Chaos]], but this claim remains unconfirmed.</center><br>
===<center>Exits</center>===
<center>Step onto the shore within the level, and once you are fully prepared, you can return to the dimension you were in before entering the level.</center><br>
</div>

<div class="blurquote-noperson blurquote-noborder" style="margin: 1em;">{{Blurquote|quote-text=Standing at the edge of reality once again.<br>The same streets. The same sound of wind, the same honking of cars.<br>Only this time, you are no longer trying to escape that dim and suffocating reality, nor to break free from that imperfect self.<br>Take a step back.<br>The gentle breeze brushes against your face, softly caressing your heart as well.<br>You were once gently held up, you were once allowed to pause, and now, you are ready to set out again.<br>Though life in the human world is bitter, you are worth it.<br>Live on, live slowly, live well.<br>You surely can.
|image=Asphyxia1.jpeg}}</div>

<br><br>
